Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper focuses on speaker verification tasks and proposes methods for learning deep speaker embeddings. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper involves training neural networks for classification tasks and fine-tuning on specific classes, which falls under the scope of natural language processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes novel approaches to learning embeddings and evaluates their performance on speaker verification tasks. 
- cs.SI (Signal Processing): The paper deals with processing audio signals for speaker verification tasks. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although the paper does not explicitly mention visual data, the proposed methods for training and fine-tuning neural networks can be applied to computer vision tasks as well.
